 test by using `assertThatThrownBy`, but I realize that a method reference can throw a NoClassDef error if bcel isn't available, so that's something to keep in mind. I’m also thinking about including `.hasCauseInstanceOf(IOException.class)`. Actually, ClassConstants will catch InvocationTargetException and throw a new IOException with the message from the exception. I need to check if the message could be null if the target throws IOException. Lastly, I must add the native init by reading native-image.properties.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_HdrwE0xPSJ2BShDQZVGm3iJ4|fc_0a426ccb7ac92c720169efdcc6ee38819c9e57934924e2c7c7", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/ant-ant-tests/native-image.properties", "edits": [{"oldText": "Args = --initialize-at-run-time=org.apache.tools.ant.AntClassLoader,org.apache.tools.ant.TaskAdapter,org.apache.tools.ant.taskdefs.Ant\n", "newText": "Args = --initialize-at-run-time=org.apache.tools.ant.AntClassLoader,org.apache.tools.ant.TaskAdapter,org.apache.tools.ant.taskdefs.Ant,org.apache.tools.ant.filters.ClassConstants\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 401, "output": 1651, "cacheRead": 50688, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 52740, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777327276476, "responseId": "resp_0a426ccb7ac92c720169efdcad0bec819cb6b7d1dc104491a5"}}
